    "nickname": "Truffles",
    "description": "Truffles is our foundation doe and matriarch of our herd. Our son purchased her from a senior 4H’r that was aging out with money he earned from selling eggs as a showmanship goat. After not settling the first year on the farm due to mineral deficiencies we got her bred in 2017. In 2018 she finally got into some open class shows and was showing some promise. In the final show of the season (Evergreen State Fair) she took GCH, Best in Show and Best Udder in a very competitive class. She also earned her AR star in 2018 making her a 2*M (2nd generation) milker. The following year 2019 she kidded with quad does and we entered her in several shows. She did well just missing the final cut. Then in June of 2019 at the Wine Country Dairy Goat Show she won all 3 rings, Best in Show and Best Udder overall! This made her a finished GCH. In the fall of 2018, she received her SG status as well. We retained 1 of her 2019 daughters, Cowgirl."
